00:19:35,846 --> 00:19:37,980
Then how about this for the next bet?

362
00:19:38,213 --> 00:19:42,297
MSC News will take the lead in viewer
rating within the next two weeks.

363
00:19:44,679 --> 00:19:46,196
That's a tough bet.

364
00:19:47,971 --> 00:19:49,854
Yeah, sure they can.

365
00:19:50,379 --> 00:19:51,277
Me too.

366
00:19:53,379 --> 00:19:55,080
-MSC win.
-Me, too.

367
00:19:58,379 --> 00:20:00,284
Since that's the company I work for...

368
00:20:01,412 --> 00:20:03,512
I have no other choice
but to stay loyal to it.

369
00:20:04,012 --> 00:20:06,126
Hwang seonbae, you're not betting
this time either, right?

370
00:20:25,913 --> 00:20:27,414
-Yeah.
-It's me, Jang Hyun-gyu.

371
00:20:27,880 --> 00:20:30,614
Choi Dal-Po hasn't back to
his assigned district yet.

372
00:20:38,358 --> 00:20:38,824
Captain

373
00:20:44,546 --> 00:20:45,768
53 missed calls

374
00:20:49,182 --> 00:20:50,566
Scrub harder.

375
00:20:55,646 --> 00:20:56,480
That's it.

376
00:20:57,613 --> 00:20:58,447
Geez...

377
00:20:59,379 --> 00:21:00,266
Oh, my.

378
00:21:01,713 --> 00:21:04,180
Who turned this bathwater so filthy?

379
00:21:05,079 --> 00:21:07,112
Is this from me, or you?

380
00:21:07,813 --> 00:21:09,514
-It's me, Father.
-Huh?

381
00:21:09,820 --> 00:21:11,563
The pressroom is a total mess.

382
00:21:11,982 --> 00:21:14,498
I don't have time to wash
my hair and brush my teeth.

383
00:21:14,589 --> 00:21:16,930
Wearing the same socks and
underwear for a week is a given.

384
00:21:18,001 --> 00:21:19,655
It really doesn't fit for any human.

385
00:21:19,746 --> 00:21:21,220
Oh, my goodness.

386
00:21:21,538 --> 00:21:25,125
It really is nasty work.

387
00:21:25,216 --> 00:21:27,449
One reporter even has a cockroach
laid its eggs on his head.

388
00:21:27,540 --> 00:21:29,789
And it's just accepted that
we'll all get athlete's foot.

389
00:21:29,880 --> 00:21:30,714
And then...

390
00:21:31,521 --> 00:21:32,355
Hey.

391
00:21:32,446 --> 00:21:33,280
Dal-Po.

392
00:21:33,688 --> 00:21:34,414
Yes?

393
00:21:36,021 --> 00:21:38,740
Shall we bathe separately?

394
00:21:39,254 --> 00:21:40,662
No, this is fine for me.

395
00:21:42,963 --> 00:21:44,639
I'm sure it's fine for you.

396
00:21:51,090 --> 00:21:52,465
Is Choi Dal-Po not coming?

397
00:21:52,585 --> 00:21:53,971
Did he quit or something?

398
00:21:54,062 --> 00:21:55,550
I don't know, he didn't answer my calls.

399
00:21:55,920 --> 00:21:56,930
I don't care.

400
00:21:57,021 --> 00:21:59,999
I guess the gym lady's story
was quite a shock to him.

401
00:22:00,254 --> 00:22:03,521
Who knew the story would have such
a tragic truth hidden behind it?

402
00:22:03,612 --> 00:22:04,504
That's what I'm saying.

403
00:22:04,595 --> 00:22:07,079
Did that Nitpicker Jang
not bust you for it?

404
00:22:07,170 --> 00:22:08,828
No, he's been very quiet.

405
00:22:08,919 --> 00:22:10,286
I thought I'd get killed.

406
00:22:11,478 --> 00:22:12,644
But that's what scares me even more.

407
00:22:15,111 --> 00:22:16,111
What's that?

408
00:22:19,745 --> 00:22:20,545
Is that a silky chicken?

409
00:22:26,344 --> 00:22:27,178
Wait!

410
00:22:27,277 --> 00:22:28,577
That's Ms Park Rosa!

411
00:22:28,668 --> 00:22:30,668
-Chairwoman of Bum-Jo Department Store.
-Really?

412
00:22:30,977 --> 00:22:31,977
That silky chicken?

413
00:22:32,977 --> 00:22:33,744
Yes, that's her.

414
00:22:33,811 --> 00:22:35,878
I'm sure since my oppa models
for that store.

415
00:22:36,010 --> 00:22:37,142
You said you're an only daughter?

416
00:22:37,233 --> 00:22:38,467
You have a model brother?

417
00:22:41,509 --> 00:22:43,784
Excuse me, but aren't you Ms Park Rosa?

418
00:22:44,246 --> 00:22:45,761
Can you tell us what brings you here?

419
00:22:45,852 --> 00:22:47,385
I came to see my son.

420
00:22:47,795 --> 00:22:48,740
Where's the pressroom?

421
00:22:49,394 --> 00:22:50,295
The pressroom?

422
00:22:51,227 --> 00:22:52,227
Your son's name is...?

423
00:22:52,394 --> 00:22:53,262
Bum-Jo.

424
00:22:53,761 --> 00:22:54,595
Seo Bum-Jo.

425
00:22:54,795 --> 00:22:55,411
What?

426
00:22:56,836 --> 00:22:58,103
He really is a conglomerate?

427
00:22:58,194 --> 00:22:59,726
-Mother.
-My son.

428
00:23:03,027 --> 00:23:03,716
My son!

429
00:23:04,528 --> 00:23:05,581
Mother, you came.

430
00:23:06,461 --> 00:23:07,083
No, Son!

431
00:23:11,528 --> 00:23:13,047
My son...

432
00:23:17,861 --> 00:23:20,021
Mother, just throw those
clothes away, please.

433
00:23:20,409 --> 00:23:22,139
They may be stylish,
but no functionality.

434
00:23:22,230 --> 00:23:23,597
They don't keep me warm at all.

435
00:23:23,805 --> 00:23:25,172
You should've told me sooner.

436
00:23:25,263 --> 00:23:28,249
How could you not say anything
until reduced down to this state?

437
00:23:29,138 --> 00:23:29,984
It's so warm.

438
00:23:31,738 --> 00:23:33,511
Mother, did you see the news last night?

439
00:23:33,611 --> 00:23:34,830
Of course, I did.

440
00:23:35,377 --> 00:23:37,964
I heard that you covered
the liver transplant story?

441
00:23:39,477 --> 00:23:41,180
I did it with In-ha.

442
00:23:41,644 --> 00:23:43,720
But you know what's so surprising?

443
00:23:44,110 --> 00:23:46,784
The ill daughter had no money for surgery

444
00:23:46,875 --> 00:23:49,608
and she lost her liver donor
since her mother died.

445
00:23:49,817 --> 00:23:51,483
But after that news aired,

446
00:23:51,574 --> 00:23:53,824
a liver donor just appeared
out of nowhere!

447
00:23:54,031 --> 00:23:54,752
Really?

448
00:23:54,843 --> 00:23:57,387
Plus, many people are sending donations.

449
00:23:57,485 --> 00:23:59,073
She didn't have to worry
about surgery fee.

450
00:23:59,851 --> 00:24:01,716
Are you that excited about it?

451
00:24:01,807 --> 00:24:03,174
Of course it's exciting.

452
00:24:03,516 --> 00:24:04,916
A word saved a person's life.

453
00:24:05,183 --> 00:24:06,195
Isn't that wonderful?

454
00:24:06,583 --> 00:24:08,069
Yes, it's wonderful.

455
00:24:08,160 --> 00:24:11,560
But I thought you'd never ask me
for any favors. What's the matter?

456
00:24:12,869 --> 00:24:14,136
It's because of In-ha.

457
00:24:14,702 --> 00:24:15,536
In-ha?

458
00:24:15,735 --> 00:24:16,636
That Pinocchio?

459
00:24:17,001 --> 00:24:17,835
Yes.

460
00:24:18,569 --> 00:24:20,569
In-ha is a little sick right now.

461
00:24:22,268 --> 00:24:24,347
Did you bring everything
that I asked for?

462
00:24:27,302 --> 00:24:28,136
Hey.

463
00:24:29,802 --> 00:24:31,469
You can't get sick in here.

464
00:24:31,569 --> 00:24:33,880
You'll get all officers and
reporters here sick too.

465
00:24:33,971 --> 00:24:35,341
I know.

466
00:24:35,432 --> 00:24:37,432
Just give me a case, instead of this.

467
00:24:39,409 --> 00:24:40,769
That would make me feel better.

468
00:24:42,390 --> 00:24:44,104
Have you heard from Dal-Po yet?

469
00:24:44,195 --> 00:24:46,295
I was just about to ask
you the same thing.

470
00:24:46,593 --> 00:24:48,260
I haven't seen him. Something happened?

471
00:24:48,493 --> 00:24:50,214
No, it's nothing.

472
00:24:54,226 --> 00:24:55,160
Who are you?

473
00:24:55,959 --> 00:24:57,059
What are you guys doing?

474
00:24:57,959 --> 00:24:58,959
Just some cleaning.

475
00:24:59,327 --> 00:25:01,232
It's a very harsh environment here.

476
00:25:01,727 --> 00:25:04,294
Please lay out the electric
pad under her spot.

477
00:25:05,460 --> 00:25:07,211
Hello, Miss Choi In-ha.

478
00:25:07,344 --> 00:25:08,892
I've heard a lot about you.

479
00:25:09,143 --> 00:25:10,477
I'm Bum-jo's mom.

480
00:25:11,177 --> 00:25:12,434
Oh, yes.

481
00:25:14,243 --> 00:25:15,211
Nice to meet you.

482
00:25:15,477 --> 00:25:16,615
Please sit down.

483
00:25:18,344 --> 00:25:22,186
Bum-Jo told me that you don't
like to spend money like this.

484
00:25:22,284 --> 00:25:25,317
But since you're sick now,
just endure even if you don't like it...

485
00:25:28,950 --> 00:25:30,317
The smell of a clean blanket.

486
00:25:30,408 --> 00:25:31,541
I feel like alive.

487
00:25:32,701 --> 00:25:35,494
Oh, this feels so warm!

488
00:25:36,384 --> 00:25:38,889
Awesome! It's a heater!

489
00:25:39,685 --> 00:25:40,553
Corn snacks.

490
00:25:40,685 --> 00:25:41,865
Chocolate bar.

491
00:25:42,111 --> 00:25:44,926
Ma'am, how did you know me so well?

492
00:25:49,484 --> 00:25:51,418
Are you sure she doesn't
like things like this?

493
00:25:51,817 --> 00:25:54,432
She must be really sick.

494
00:26:01,084 --> 00:26:03,052
I don't think the reporter is something
a human being should do.

495
00:26:04,318 --> 00:26:05,152
Eat this.

496
00:26:06,451 --> 00:26:08,363
I have to take a cab when I do mawari.

497
00:26:08,454 --> 00:26:11,322
I heard one month of taxi fare
and a phone bill is nearly 2000 dollars.

498
00:26:11,428 --> 00:26:13,296
But I have to pay for
those with my own money.

499
00:26:13,362 --> 00:26:14,429
Does it even make sense?

500
00:26:14,695 --> 00:26:16,593
No, that's ridiculous.

501
00:26:18,295 --> 00:26:19,428
Father...

502
00:26:19,729 --> 00:26:21,468
I can't keep up with this
nonsense anymore.

503
00:26:21,559 --> 00:26:23,542
We avoid poop not because
we're afraid, because it's filthy.

504
00:26:23,633 --> 00:26:24,467
That's right.

505
00:26:24,544 --> 00:26:25,684
Just quit.

506
00:26:26,775 --> 00:26:29,774
Why bother doing something so absurd?

507
00:26:30,578 --> 00:26:31,412
But...

508
00:26:32,244 --> 00:26:35,173
you got that proverb flipped around.

509
00:26:35,711 --> 00:26:38,278
We avoid poop not because it's filthy,

510
00:26:38,369 --> 00:26:40,646
it's because we're afraid of it.

511
00:26:40,811 --> 00:26:43,264
No, you've got it flipped around.

512
00:26:43,355 --> 00:26:45,101
We avoid poop because it's filthy.

513
00:26:45,311 --> 00:26:47,684
No, it's not.

514
00:26:47,944 --> 00:26:49,543
But if that's the case,

515
00:26:49,778 --> 00:26:51,845
if the poop is filthy,

516
00:26:52,077 --> 00:26:54,210
someone who cleans it
who wants avoids it the most.

517
00:26:57,778 --> 00:26:59,442
Sure you afraid.

518
00:26:59,845 --> 00:27:01,312
Since its dirt might rub off on you.

519
00:27:01,411 --> 00:27:03,538
You certainly avoid it since you afraid.

520
00:27:06,611 --> 00:27:09,479
My mom wasn't losing the weight
because she wants to get pretty.

521
00:27:10,111 --> 00:27:11,878
Mom...

522
00:27:13,311 --> 00:27:14,311
I'm sorry.

523
00:27:16,044 --> 00:27:17,344
I'm so very sorry.

524
00:27:20,144 --> 00:27:21,244
Yes, Father.

525
00:27:24,211 --> 00:27:25,964
The truth is, I ran because I scared.

526
00:27:26,711 --> 00:27:27,545
Right?

527
00:27:28,077 --> 00:27:30,139
You had it flipped around,
and I had it right.

528
00:27:30,678 --> 00:27:33,919
You're avoiding the poop
because you're scared.

529
00:27:35,177 --> 00:27:38,478
I run at it, thinking I could
just clean up that poop.

530
00:27:39,211 --> 00:27:40,244
But that wasn't it.

531
00:27:41,211 --> 00:27:42,712
Being a reporter scared me.

532
00:27:43,745 --> 00:27:45,045
It was much scarier...

533
00:27:46,277 --> 00:27:47,412
than I ever thought.

534
00:27:47,944 --> 00:27:48,944
Really?

535
00:27:49,411 --> 00:27:50,645
Then, you'll be fine now.

536
00:27:53,344 --> 00:27:54,178
I beg your pardon?

537
00:27:54,711 --> 00:27:57,545
It's a problem if you run at something
without knowing to be fearful of it.

538
00:27:57,636 --> 00:28:00,205
But you'll be fine as long as you know it.

539
00:28:01,544 --> 00:28:03,811
You won't get into a big trouble anymore.

540
00:28:09,044 --> 00:28:11,783
Eat this tail and cheer up.

541
00:28:13,977 --> 00:28:14,733
Yes, Father.

542
00:28:15,244 --> 00:28:16,670
Father, this is just so unfair.

543
00:28:19,244 --> 00:28:21,489
You only care about your first-born
and you always forget me.

544
00:28:21,745 --> 00:28:23,646
Hurry up and come here.

545
00:28:23,811 --> 00:28:25,512
Come and have a seat.

546
00:28:27,811 --> 00:28:29,939
There's plenty of eel.

547
00:28:30,977 --> 00:28:32,110
But there's no tail.

548
00:28:32,177 --> 00:28:33,611
No tail!

549
00:28:47,803 --> 00:28:50,337
Nitpicker Jang, Yoon Yoo-Rae,
Ahn Chan-soo, Captain

550
00:28:51,465 --> 00:28:53,813
Niece In-ha

551
00:28:59,077 --> 00:29:01,478
Let's be reporters together, In-ha.

552
00:29:17,277 --> 00:29:19,245
I'm Choi Dal-Po, trainee
for Han River district.

553
00:29:19,378 --> 00:29:20,612
I will return now.

554
00:29:24,811 --> 00:29:26,278
Why are you standing here like that?

555
00:29:28,711 --> 00:29:31,945
Choi Dal-Po disappeared for a while
and now he's on his way back here.

556
00:29:32,478 --> 00:29:33,611
So? What about it?

557
00:29:33,877 --> 00:29:34,711
I mean...

558
00:29:35,144 --> 00:29:37,158
You know, most trainees throws a fit

559
00:29:37,411 --> 00:29:39,676
or hands in their resignation
after having disappeared.

560
00:29:40,378 --> 00:29:41,796
I doubt that.

561
00:29:42,010 --> 00:29:44,267
Choi Dal-Po didn't seem that way to me.

562
00:29:45,511 --> 00:29:47,503
You can't judge him by his appearance.

563
00:29:48,611 --> 00:29:50,811
I heard that Mr Head
Department who looks calm

564
00:29:50,845 --> 00:29:54,457
threatened his superiors, pretending to
jump off the roof when he was a trainee.

565
00:29:54,548 --> 00:29:56,681
I'm going to kill myself!

566
00:29:56,772 --> 00:29:58,172
Just calm down.

567
00:29:59,004 --> 00:30:01,207
Hey, hey, Won-goo!

568
00:30:01,298 --> 00:30:05,353
Oh, my. If we're going to talk about
that, then you are the champion.

569
00:30:06,423 --> 00:30:07,597
Daddy, it's him!

570
00:30:08,088 --> 00:30:09,863
How dare you torment my son!

571
00:30:13,798 --> 00:30:16,214
Your father came to the office

572
00:30:16,305 --> 00:30:19,215
and threw snakes at Hwang Gyo-dong
since you told him he was tormenting you.

573
00:30:19,306 --> 00:30:21,614
Would I did that if he
didn't bug me persistently?

574
00:30:21,705 --> 00:30:23,424
Oh, is that right?

575
00:30:23,681 --> 00:30:25,556
Then I guess you were
bugging Choi Dal-Po, too?

576
00:30:25,647 --> 00:30:26,847
Enough for him to throw a fit?

577
00:30:27,681 --> 00:30:29,869
Well, I was just trying to be...

578
00:30:36,581 --> 00:30:37,368
You came.

579
00:30:40,514 --> 00:30:42,608
I apologize for the trouble I've caused.

580
00:30:42,699 --> 00:30:44,574
Go in. Captain is waiting for you.

581
00:30:45,408 --> 00:30:46,242
Yes, Sir.

582
00:30:47,580 --> 00:30:48,074
Yeah.

583
00:30:52,942 --> 00:30:55,844
Don't talk back even you get scolded
and don't cry either...

584
00:30:56,475 --> 00:30:56,992
Oh, my.

585
00:30:57,727 --> 00:30:59,142
You just worry about yourself.

586
00:31:01,575 --> 00:31:02,443
I was just...

587
00:31:11,942 --> 00:31:12,776
You're back.

588
00:31:13,908 --> 00:31:14,742
I'm sorry.

589
00:31:15,074 --> 00:31:16,274
I have no excuses.

590
00:31:16,708 --> 00:31:17,530
What I did was wrong.

591
00:31:17,942 --> 00:31:18,858
As long as you aware.

592
00:31:18,949 --> 00:31:20,034
Get back to your district.

593
00:31:20,125 --> 00:31:21,034
Pardon me?

594
00:31:24,188 --> 00:31:25,108
Yes, Sir.

595
00:31:31,541 --> 00:31:32,727
Is that it?

596
00:31:33,274 --> 00:31:35,186
I came fully prepared to be disciplined.

597
00:31:35,252 --> 00:31:36,475
It was a pretty big mistake

598
00:31:36,566 --> 00:31:38,311
just to be let off the
hook so easily, indeed.

599
00:31:38,410 --> 00:31:40,130
Then, why are you letting it slide?

600
00:31:40,262 --> 00:31:41,484
You get one chance.

601
00:31:42,262 --> 00:31:44,230
Since I've made a similar mistake myself.

602
00:31:45,296 --> 00:31:46,164
A similar...

603
00:31:47,029 --> 00:31:47,863
...mistake?

604
00:31:48,029 --> 00:31:48,863
Yeah.

605
00:31:49,396 --> 00:31:50,912
Thirteen years ago...

606
00:31:51,429 --> 00:31:54,429
I imprecisely portrayed
the head of a family as a murderer

607
00:31:55,296 --> 00:31:56,630
and because of that news

608
00:31:57,496 --> 00:31:59,430
the whole family was tragically ruined.

609
00:32:06,629 --> 00:32:07,629
Then...

610
00:32:09,429 --> 00:32:11,196
how did you ever overcome it?

611
00:32:13,329 --> 00:32:14,396
I couldn't.

612
00:32:15,129 --> 00:32:16,496
I ran away, just like you did.

613
00:32:17,262 --> 00:32:18,429
I quit being a reporter.

614
00:32:19,696 --> 00:32:21,405
I moved to another department
and become a producer.

615
00:32:21,496 --> 00:32:22,696
And five years later...

616
00:32:25,962 --> 00:32:28,905
I met the son of that man on a quiz show.

617
00:32:35,763 --> 00:32:37,615
Then why did you come back as a reporter?

618
00:32:39,663 --> 00:32:41,063
Because seeing that man's son...

619
00:32:43,096 --> 00:32:44,096
...made me ashamed.

620
00:32:46,181 --> 00:32:48,356
As if he caught me hiding
because I was scared.

621
00:32:50,730 --> 00:32:52,531
That's why I came back
to news department.

622
00:32:55,229 --> 00:32:56,496
How did it feel to come back?

623
00:32:58,629 --> 00:32:59,463
Is reporter...

624
00:33:01,262 --> 00:33:02,421
...something you can do?

625
00:33:06,862 --> 00:33:08,257
I feel like my whole body

626
00:33:08,629 --> 00:33:11,252
is being pricked by thousands of needles.

627
00:33:17,696 --> 00:33:20,130
Isn't this the first flu
you've had since high school?

628
00:33:20,763 --> 00:33:21,432
Yeah.

629
00:33:24,596 --> 00:33:26,086
But how did you know that?

630
00:33:28,363 --> 00:33:30,518
You told me that awhile back.

631
00:33:30,730 --> 00:33:32,997
Anyway, I think this flu is no joke.

632
00:33:33,096 --> 00:33:34,897
Let's tell seonbae and
take you to the hospital.

633
00:33:34,988 --> 00:33:35,822
-Okay?
-No.

634
00:33:37,029 --> 00:33:38,396
I just barely make points.

635
00:33:38,529 --> 00:33:40,363
I can't lose it over the simple flu.

636
00:33:41,329 --> 00:33:43,563
But I don't even have the strength
to move my fingers.

637
00:33:45,329 --> 00:33:46,263
Chan-soo!

638
00:33:46,995 --> 00:33:47,829
Choi In-ha.

639
00:33:50,929 --> 00:33:52,029
What's that?

640
00:33:52,296 --> 00:33:54,644
An investigation report?
Or a case report?

641
00:33:54,735 --> 00:33:55,735
Are you going to get approval?

642
00:33:56,509 --> 00:33:58,273
Get away! You can get me catch a cold.

643
00:33:59,714 --> 00:34:00,844
Tell me about it first.

644
00:34:00,943 --> 00:34:02,476
I'll get you catch a cold
if you don't tell me.

645
00:34:03,954 --> 00:34:05,728
It's nothing, just a phone call log.

646
00:34:05,819 --> 00:34:06,919
What call log?

647
00:34:08,977 --> 00:34:11,650
It's the recent container fire case's
suspect, Moon Duk-soo's call log.

648
00:34:11,741 --> 00:34:13,191
You won't understand even if you see it.

649
00:34:13,282 --> 00:34:15,079
We might need it down the road.

650
00:34:15,377 --> 00:34:16,868
Seo Bum-Jo, take a picture.

651
00:34:16,959 --> 00:34:17,516
Okay!

652
00:34:18,344 --> 00:34:19,279
No, you can't have it.

653
00:34:29,880 --> 00:34:31,809
Customer name: Moon Duk-soo

654
00:34:33,077 --> 00:34:34,900
Outgoing Calls

655
00:34:36,410 --> 00:34:38,044
Moon Duk-soo's call log.

656
00:34:38,344 --> 00:34:39,267
Choi Dal-Po.

657
00:34:39,358 --> 00:34:40,425
Are you back now?

658
00:34:40,791 --> 00:34:41,338
Yeah.

659
00:34:42,458 --> 00:34:44,238
You just memorized
the whole list, didn't you?

660
00:34:44,724 --> 00:34:45,658
Maybe.

661
00:34:46,290 --> 00:34:47,157
In-ha.

662
00:34:47,357 --> 00:34:48,197
We need to talk.

663
00:34:48,524 --> 00:34:51,228
In-ha seems to have much
to say to you, anyway.

664
00:34:51,457 --> 00:34:53,053
She kept looking for
you while you're away.

665
00:34:54,323 --> 00:34:56,224
I have nothing to say.

666
00:34:58,590 --> 00:35:00,890
We have to go to Traffic
Accident Department.

667
00:35:02,357 --> 00:35:03,865
Okay, let's go.

668
00:35:06,190 --> 00:35:07,290
What's wrong with her?

669
00:35:07,381 --> 00:35:08,648
It's like she's avoiding you.

670
00:35:09,090 --> 00:35:11,024
Yeah. She is avoiding me.

671
00:35:12,290 --> 00:35:13,124
Why?

672
00:35:13,857 --> 00:35:15,624
I said some things I shouldn't have said.

673
00:35:16,990 --> 00:35:18,724
You still haven't fixed that habit?

674
00:35:18,824 --> 00:35:21,057
Back in high school, you used to say...

675
00:35:21,490 --> 00:35:22,589
You have to let me finish, man!

676
00:35:22,680 --> 00:35:24,980
That's why people says you're rude, man!

677
00:35:26,424 --> 00:35:27,358
Come on, hyungnim.

678
00:35:27,590 --> 00:35:30,362
We just saw a wrecker come in.
How can you say there was no accident?

679
00:35:31,190 --> 00:35:33,522
-What kind of an accident was it?
-I told you it was nothing.

680
00:35:33,857 --> 00:35:35,391
We're investigating it now,
so come back later.

681
00:35:35,891 --> 00:35:37,892
I promise we'll be back later.

682
00:35:40,106 --> 00:35:41,118
In-ha.

683
00:35:41,209 --> 00:35:42,043
In-ha!

684
00:35:45,417 --> 00:35:46,251
I'm okay.

685
00:35:47,451 --> 00:35:48,760
Where do we have to go next?

686
00:35:50,751 --> 00:35:52,370
We have to go around
the precinct station.

687
00:35:53,760 --> 00:35:54,860
You think you can manage?

688
00:35:54,951 --> 00:35:56,151
I told you that I'm fine.

689
00:35:56,618 --> 00:35:57,493
This won't do.

690
00:35:57,584 --> 00:35:58,684
I'm going to call my mom.

691
00:35:58,751 --> 00:35:59,585
Are you out of your mind?

692
00:36:00,785 --> 00:36:02,889
Who would do mawari with a luxurious car?

693
00:36:02,980 --> 00:36:04,165
We'd get in a lot of trouble.

694
00:36:04,950 --> 00:36:06,841
I'll take your punishment,
so don't worry.

695
00:36:14,997 --> 00:36:17,127
New police of hope carries
out duty to the fullest

696
00:36:17,218 --> 00:36:18,365
Hey, Choi Dal-Po!

697
00:36:18,456 --> 00:36:20,064
Why you didn't answer my calls?

698
00:36:20,155 --> 00:36:22,255
Do you know how hard it was for
me to do all the work by myself?

699
00:36:27,097 --> 00:36:27,631
What the heck?

700
00:36:28,030 --> 00:36:29,085
That Chairman came back?

701
00:36:29,896 --> 00:36:30,897
Watch your head.

702
00:36:31,453 --> 00:36:32,320
Where are those two going?

703
00:36:42,530 --> 00:36:43,530
No way!

704
00:36:44,130 --> 00:36:45,836
They're doing mawari with that car?

705
00:36:47,063 --> 00:36:47,897
Yeah.

706
00:36:49,220 --> 00:36:50,766
I'm so jealous!

707
00:36:51,297 --> 00:36:52,198
That must be nice.

708
00:36:52,397 --> 00:36:55,304
She's partnered up with a rich boy,
and making her rounds in a nice car.

709
00:36:56,797 --> 00:37:00,164
All I got was a trashy partner who makes
me do all the hard work by myself.

710
00:37:01,263 --> 00:37:03,770
I'm sorry for being a trashy partner.

711
00:37:08,084 --> 00:37:08,871
As long as you know.

712
00:37:10,163 --> 00:37:11,196
Do you have anything to report?

713
00:37:11,820 --> 00:37:13,692
No, they're all minor stuff.

714
00:37:13,938 --> 00:37:15,531
Just tell me even though it's all minor.

715
00:37:16,726 --> 00:37:18,978
Just a simple DUI case.
That's already been reported.

716
00:37:19,927 --> 00:37:21,741
Your friend gave me this one,
but I'm passing on it.

717
00:37:22,030 --> 00:37:24,471
Hey, I'm not passing on anything anymore.

718
00:37:24,562 --> 00:37:26,562
-Just tell me.
-It's about that container fire.

719
00:37:26,630 --> 00:37:27,539
Nothing much to it.

720
00:37:27,630 --> 00:37:29,235
That suspect on the run, Moon Duk-soo.

721
00:37:29,506 --> 00:37:31,164
He's actually someone we know.

722
00:37:31,464 --> 00:37:32,731
-Someone we know?
-Yeah.

723
00:37:33,096 --> 00:37:35,506
You know the factory explosion
news we saw during our interview?

724
00:37:35,597 --> 00:37:38,383
Remember Mr Moon from the interview who
said that he tried to stop the Fire Chief?

725
00:37:39,464 --> 00:37:40,298
It's him.

726
00:37:41,929 --> 00:37:45,998
The Chief insisted
to go in there aimlessly.

727
00:37:46,831 --> 00:37:48,157
It's nothing. I just amazed.

728
00:37:49,464 --> 00:37:50,631
That's him?

729
00:37:54,197 --> 00:37:55,197
Thank you.

730
00:37:55,530 --> 00:37:57,203
You really don't have to do all this.

731
00:37:57,732 --> 00:37:59,107
Of course, I should.

732
00:37:59,198 --> 00:38:00,238
Since it's my son's request.

733
00:38:00,730 --> 00:38:01,564
Don't worry.

734
00:38:01,929 --> 00:38:04,678
I'll get you all the cases tonight.

735
00:38:13,058 --> 00:38:15,231
Thank you all for your hard work.

736
00:38:16,096 --> 00:38:17,730
Are there any cases today?

737
00:38:18,597 --> 00:38:21,422
-I beg your pardon?
-My son is a reporter.

738
00:38:21,513 --> 00:38:23,013
He's looking for a case
that he can report on.

739
00:38:25,268 --> 00:38:26,129
Oh, this is for you.

740
00:38:26,421 --> 00:38:26,950
Yes.

741
00:38:30,766 --> 00:38:31,600
Anything?

742
00:38:33,166 --> 00:38:34,433
How can there not be any cases?

743
00:38:34,524 --> 00:38:35,993
Crimes are committed everywhere.

744
00:38:36,084 --> 00:38:37,560
Just take a look at the news.

745
00:38:37,651 --> 00:38:39,851
Where do you think those news surged up?

746
00:38:39,942 --> 00:38:41,543
This is where they all surged up.

747
00:38:43,584 --> 00:38:44,418
Oh my.

748
00:38:44,651 --> 00:38:46,110
Sir.

749
00:38:49,351 --> 00:38:50,906
So tell me...

750
00:38:51,084 --> 00:38:55,004
Why did you get drunk and
smash the billboard sign?

751
00:38:56,850 --> 00:39:00,104
You must have a reason.

752
00:39:01,151 --> 00:39:02,219
Hey!

753
00:39:02,484 --> 00:39:03,770
Tell me.

754
00:39:05,051 --> 00:39:08,752
There was a DUI case by a college
student at Junghwa Police Station.

755
00:39:08,884 --> 00:39:10,578
His blood alcohol level was...

756
00:39:10,669 --> 00:39:12,087
0.06 percent.

757
00:39:12,178 --> 00:39:14,461
...0.06 percent which will have
his driver license revoked...

758
00:39:15,112 --> 00:39:15,882
License suspended.

759
00:39:16,289 --> 00:39:17,711
I mean, his license...

760
00:39:18,278 --> 00:39:19,411
...suspended.

761
00:39:19,836 --> 00:39:21,479
Yes, I understand.

762
00:39:24,853 --> 00:39:26,613
Thank you, Ma'am.

763
00:39:27,244 --> 00:39:29,411
I was able to make the
report, all thanks to you.

764
00:39:29,945 --> 00:39:30,779
That's good to hear.

765
00:39:30,879 --> 00:39:33,145
Since we're done in Junghwa district,

766
00:39:33,255 --> 00:39:36,255
now take us to police
station in Eungam district.

767
00:39:36,346 --> 00:39:37,472
Yes, Ma'am.

768
00:39:38,912 --> 00:39:39,746
Mother.

769
00:39:40,146 --> 00:39:41,711
Let's go back to Han River Police Station.

770
00:39:41,802 --> 00:39:43,776
I think she needs to get some rest
at the pressroom.

771
00:39:44,379 --> 00:39:45,602
No, I'm fine.

772
00:39:45,702 --> 00:39:46,455
I am totally fine.

773
00:39:46,546 --> 00:39:48,006
No, you're not.

774
00:39:48,097 --> 00:39:50,203
You'll only interfere our job.
Just go back.

775
00:39:50,294 --> 00:39:52,560
My mother and I can handle the rest.

776
00:39:52,627 --> 00:39:54,192
Yeah, that sounds like a good idea.

777
00:39:54,283 --> 00:39:55,375
Go get some rest.

778
00:39:55,466 --> 00:39:58,533
-Mr Jung, Han River Police Station.
-Yes, Ma'am.

779
00:40:24,888 --> 00:40:26,551
Toilet seat

780
00:40:30,475 --> 00:40:31,865
It feels warm.

781
00:40:58,308 --> 00:40:59,659
Why is a girl sleeping there?

782
00:40:59,750 --> 00:41:00,983
I think she's a reporter.

783
00:41:01,074 --> 00:41:02,042
I wonder if she's sick.

784
00:41:07,197 --> 00:41:08,967
-Choi In-ha!
-Don't come near me.

785
00:41:09,058 --> 00:41:10,306
Don't come near me. Go away!

786
00:41:10,397 --> 00:41:11,231
Be quiet.

787
00:41:12,181 --> 00:41:13,949
Hey, put me down.

788
00:41:15,847 --> 00:41:16,707
Get away from me.

789
